# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — SECURITY-FIRST
#
# This repo designs a service for a highly regulated environment (GDPR · LGPD ·
# HIPAA · PCI-DSS · SOC2 · FedRAMP). Per ADR-0001 (§6 Data Protection, §10 Audit,
# §11 Secrets & Key Mgmt, §17 Privacy) and ADR-0002 (Supply Chain), the following
# must NEVER enter version control: secrets, cryptographic keys, access tokens,
# tokenization mappings, raw regulated data (PHI/PCI/PII), and audit logs.
#
# Posture: deny broadly. A blocked-but-legitimate file (e.g. a PUBLIC cert) can be
# force-added intentionally with:  git add -f <path>
# Defense in depth: this is a backstop, NOT the only control — also run a secret
# scanner (gitleaks / git-secrets) in pre-commit and CI (ADR-0002 §4).
#
# NOTE: git does NOT support trailing/inline comments — every comment is on its
# own line so no pattern is accidentally broken.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Secrets, credentials & environment files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
*.env
*secret*
*secrets*
*credential*
*credentials*
*password*
*.secret
secrets/
.secrets/
# Terraform vars routinely hold secrets:
*.tfvars
*.tfvars.json
# Allow documented, non-secret templates (force-added if matched above):
!.env.example
!*.env.example
!*.tfvars.example

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Cryptographic keys & keystores (ADR-0001 §11 — keys never leave the boundary)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
# Java keystore / truststore:
*.jks
*.keystore
*.truststore
*.asc
*.gpg
*.pgp
id_rsa*
id_dsa*
id_ecdsa*
id_ed25519*
*_rsa
*_dsa
*.ppk
.ssh/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2b. Certificates — public certs are not secret, but block by default and
#     force-add intentionally (git add -f) to avoid committing a private key by mistake.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.crt
*.cer
*.der

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Tokens, sessions & identity material (ADR-0001 §5 — OIDC/DPoP/mTLS, RFC 8693)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.jwt
*.token
*token*
# Private JWKS / signing keys — publish only public sets, force-add if needed:
jwks*.json
dpop*.key
*.session

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. Cloud / KMS / Vault / IaC state & secret material (ADR-0001 §11, §12)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.aws/
.azure/
.gcloud/
gcloud-*.json
*service-account*.json
*sa-key*.json
kubeconfig
*.kubeconfig
.kube/
vault-token
.vault-token
*.hcl.secret
# Terraform / OpenTofu state can contain plaintext secrets:
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
.terraform/
.terraform.lock.hcl
crash.log
# Helm-secrets / sops decrypted output:
*secrets*.yaml
*.dec.yaml
*.dec.json

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. Tokenization mappings & DLP findings (ADR-0001 §6, §17 — never commit)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*token-map*
*tokenization*
token_mappings/
dlp-findings/
*.dlp

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. Regulated data — PHI / PCI / PII (ADR-0001 §24; unknown data = Restricted).
#    Raw payloads, DB dumps, exports, DSAR bundles must never be committed.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.dump
*.bak
*.sql
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.db
dump/
dumps/
backups/
exports/
*export*.csv
*export*.json
phi/
pci/
pii/
restricted/
dsar/
# Packet captures may contain regulated data in transit:
*.pcap

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 7. Audit & log output (ADR-0001 §10 — WORM is the system of record, not git)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
logs/
audit/
*.audit
otel-*.json
*.trace

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 8. Build artifacts & dependencies (polyglot: Go · Java · Rust · Node — ADR-0001 §1)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Go
bin/
*.exe
*.test
*.out
# Java (Maven / Gradle)
target/
build/
.gradle/
*.class
*.jar
*.war
# Rust (Cargo)
**/*.rs.bk
# Node
node_modules/
dist/
.npm/
*.tgz

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 9. Containers & supply-chain scan output (ADR-0002 — SBOM/scan are artifacts)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.sbom
*.sbom.json
sbom-*.json
# CycloneDX / SPDX SBOMs:
*.cdx.json
*.spdx.json
trivy-results.*
grype-*.json
.cosign/
# Detached signatures — produced by the pipeline, not committed:
*.sig

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 10. Local tooling, OS & editor cruft
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/
*.tmp
*.temp
tmp/
.cache/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 11. Claude Code — keep shared config, ignore per-user local overrides
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.claude/settings.local.json
